wal of its forces from <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION> by 1990 and has begun a partial pullout of 50,000 troops and withdrawn top military command. <PERSON> Ahmed </PERSON> said it will take some time for the different parties to give final reactions to the document. He said it may provide some input for the informal talks scheduled for July 25 in <LOCATION> Indonesia </LOCATION>. The Sihanouk-led coalition and <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> have already agreed to take part in the talks but there has been no final word from the pro-Hanoi government in <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION>. The official Cambodian news agency <ORGANIZATION> SPK </ORGANIZATION> said Friday that <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON> received an invitation but did not say whether the government would attend.
