 Fearing a loss of identity, not to mention overworked index fingers, a number of <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> towns are waging a last-ditch battle against their banishment from the 617 area code. Those digits have become synonymous with high technology, urban sophistication and progressive politics, town officials say, while the new 508 area code is strictly for hicks. On July 16, approximately 190 communities in central and eastern <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> are slated to switch from 617 into 508. <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> says that the new area code is unavoidable.
